paragraphs.title: 6 - Split the Customers into Repeaters and Single Use Customers
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

repeaters = customer_counts.filter("count > 1").rdd.map(lambda x: x['customer']).collect()
singles = customer_counts.filter("count == 1").rdd.map(lambda x: x['customer']).collect()

paragraphs.title: 7 - Create two separate datasets: one for repeaters and one for singles
8 - Split the datasets for training and testing purposes
9 - Join the training and testing datasets
10 - Perform Hyper-Parameter Tuning
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=['total_items','discount%','weekday','hour','Food%','Fresh%','Drinks%','Home%','Beauty%','Health%','Baby%','Pets%'],outputCol='features')
rf = RandomForestClassifier()
params = ParamGridBuilder().addGrid(rf.maxDepth,[10,20]).addGrid(rf.numTrees,[10,20]).build()
evaluator = MulticlassClassificationEvaluator(metricName='f1')
cv = CrossValidator(estimator=rf, estimatorParamMaps=params,evaluator=evaluator,numFolds=3,parallelism=4)
pipe = Pipeline(stages=[assembler,cv])
